race.comment: GET OUT MICK (6) came off stronger city and provincial races and turned things around winning easily over 1200m at Mt Magnet. Thrown in again with the 4kg claim and he can go on with the job. THE COOLAKIN KING (2) made it back-to-back wins when successful last start over 1200m at Carnarvon. Perfectly placed again and is sure to give this a mighty shake. TEABISCUIT (9) will find this easier than Belmont Park. Has good early speed so should take up a forward position. Will be in this for a long way. SOARING SOLO (3) maintained her good record on dirt Carnarvon and Junction and then was outgraded at Belmont Park. Has a 3kg claim in easier and can get back on track. IMA WILD GIRL (5) would be a hope putting it all together.
